      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "As a generalization of the pairing mechanism responsible for the MR Pfaffian state, Read and Rezayi [CITATION_1] proposed a guiding principle for the FQH states in higher Landau levels, according to which the FQH states at ν = k/(k + 2) can be generated as the zero-energy ground state of the fermionic (k + 1)-body δ-function interaction Hamiltonian, where k is a positive integer.",
